a note on the confinement problem.wthis note explores the problem of confininga program during its execution so that it cannot transmit information to any other program except itscaller.  a set of examples attempts to stake out the boundaries of the problem.  necessary conditionsfor a solution are stated and informally justified.cacm october, lampson, b. w..kprotection, confinement, proprietary program,privacy, security, leakage of data.c. .ca jb january ,   : am